                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/9907: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-04-12T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >April 12, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1415. The Berlin afternoon press publishes a brief military communiqué stating
                    that German troops have established contact with Italian forces north of Lake
                    Ochrida and a congratulatory telegram from Hitler to Mussolini has been
                    sent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
